This frame allows one to enable/disable the display of Rulers and Straight
Edges in the Layout Form.  Rulers are section markers with a tick mark
every fifth column and a digit every tenth column.  Straight Edges are a pair
of lines (one vertical and one horizontal) that can be used to line up
components on a column or row basis.

To enable the display of Rulers or Straight Edges, enter a "y" into the
appropriate field.  Entering an "n" will disable (i.e., remove) the display
of Rulers or Straight Edges.

The menu commands are:

        MENU COMMANDS   SYNOPSIS
        -------------   --------
        Cancel          Return to the Form Layout menu, without changing
                        the display of Rulers and Straight Edges.

        Help            Access the Ingres Help facility.

        End             Return to the Form Layout menu, changing the display
                        of Rulers and Straight Edges as specified in the form.
